LA 💜

For early detection, prevention, and peace of mind. 🤍 I did a full body MRI scan when I had a scare and as an advanced bday gift for myself. 🙏🏼

Why is it important to do this scan if you can?

1. @prenuvo scans 26 regions & organs of the body.🩻 It detects cancer, tumors as small as 1cm, aneurysm, Alzheimer’s, and 500 conditions in its earliest stages

2. Only takes an hour. ⏰

3. Comfortable. Watch movies or listen to music during the scan 🎬

4. You can do it in from different cities including NYC, LA, Dallas, & Chicago

5. Use “V4M4U” to save $200 🏷️

6. Not an ad. I researched well, paid for this, and actually wish I’ve done it sooner

Hoping for the day when no one will ever have to say, “we caught it too late.”

Take advantage of today’s technology. 💯 Share with family & loved ones 🤗

𝙒𝙝𝙖𝙩 𝙬𝙚 𝙢𝙚𝙖𝙣 𝙗𝙮 ‘𝙂𝙞𝙧𝙡 𝙏𝙝𝙚𝙧𝙖𝙥𝙮’ ✨ First time trying a Korean Facial in the DMV. 😍 Honest Review:

🌟 Loved the variety of Korean technology skincare devices used such as: O2toDERM oxygen therapy, LED therapy, Local Dynamic Micro-massage, High-intensity Focused Ultrasound

💯 Technicians explained the treatments with in-depth details. They’ll make sure you’re learning & can take care of your skin better after the session.

👍🏼 1st session with the Head Technician went great! Her facial massages were nothing short of AMAZING

😬 2nd session was with a different technician. Compared to the first, her facial massages lacked depth and wasn’t as relaxing (I’m a sucker for massages)

🙁 They don’t do manual extractions? They used a steamer to start but it wasn’t enough for stubborn whiteheads. I can still feel the hard whitehead bumps that weren’t removed from the 1st session so I made sure to ask on the 2nd session. I was surprised the technician used her nails instead of a precised extraction tool (although gloved, my dermatologist would be mad 😂). Long story short, she still couldn’t remove them and I had to do it myself at home.

💰For $700 2-session package, I was expecting consistency on techniques and clearer pores after extraction.

Real question is: did my skin improve? 𝗔 𝗵𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗰𝗲𝗻𝘁! 💯 I have very dry skin and winters are usually the hardest for me. But it’s been weeks now, and my skin feels softer and visibly brighter. I love being a girly girl haha. Let this be a reminder to moisturize, moisturize, moisturize 🫶🏻

📍 @klarspastudios in Fairfax
